          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">The prefrontal cortex mediates moral reasoning. The insula drives empathy. The amygdala calibrates threat response. If a BCI can modulate these structures, it can alter a person's ethical judgment itself. This branch tells us which neural pathways require the highest protection tier.</p>
